Brenda Finn was diagnosed with alopecia universalis at the age of 14 . 
  She suffered from crippling anxiety and depression after losing her hair and fingernails . 
  She was bullied at school for wearing a wig and was forced to leave school . 
  Miss Finn says having eyebrows tattooed on has given her confidence . 
  She is calling for medical tattooing to become available on the NHS . 
  She says it could have saved her years of emotional pain . 
 